# Airline Data Pipeline

## Overview
This project demonstrates a complete data engineering pipeline using Docker, processing Airline On-Time Performance data.

## Components
- SFTP Server: Simulates data source
- Data Ingestion: Retrieves files from SFTP
- Data Processing: Cleans and transforms flight data
- API: Provides access to processed data

## Prerequisites
- Docker
- Docker Compose

## Setup and Run
1. Clone the repository
2. Place sample flight data CSV files in `data/sample_flights/`
3. Run: `docker-compose up --build`

## API Usage
Endpoint: `http://localhost:5000/flights`

### Parameters
- `start_date`: Filter flights from this date
- `end_date`: Filter flights until this date
- `cursor`: Pagination cursor
- `limit`: Number of records per page (default 100)

### Authentication
- Username: `apiuser`
- Password: Set in `docker-compose.yml`

## Error Handling
- Logs maintained in respective service containers
- Robust error handling in ingestion and processing scripts

## Data Processing
- Combines multiple CSV files
- Cleans and transforms data
- Categorizes flight performance